Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.67,0:00:32.78,black-small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(542.286,239.143)}pebbles
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.54,0:00:38.58,black-small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(334.857,183.714)}Maybe if I...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.00,0:01:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,｢a crow can think｣
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.00,0:01:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,｢can think... can think｣
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.00,0:01:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Observe, propose a hypothesis, experiment and consider results.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.00,0:01:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Learn the way of scientific thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.29,0:01:25.30,black-large,,0,0,0,,{\pos(314,136)}Thinking Crow
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.29,0:01:25.30,black-small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(324,255)}thinking scientifically
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.40,0:01:33.21,white-large,,0,0,0,,{\pos(399,126)}Thinking\NObservation
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.00,0:01:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We begin with a Thinking Observation.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.00,0:01:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Today we observe a strange phenomenon using coins.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.00,0:01:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold a single 1 yen and two 10 yen coins between your fingers.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.00,0:01:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The topmost 10 yen coin will remain in our fingers.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.12,0:02:02.43,white-small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(173,111)}don't drop
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.46,0:02:02.43,white-small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(174,168)}one yen
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.40,0:02:02.43,white-small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(185,222)}ten yen
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.00,0:01:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Then drop the lower two coins.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.00,0:02:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Arranged with he 1 yen coin above and the 10 yen coin below.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.00,0:02:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If we drop these two coins...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.00,0:02:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The 1 yen coin ends up on bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.00,0:02:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Did they switch places while falling?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.00,0:02:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do that once more.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.00,0:02:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Once more time the 1 yen coin ends up on the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.00,0:02:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,As we thought they switched positions.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.00,0:02:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's try a different combination.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.00,0:02:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We add another 10 yen coin underneath.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.00,0:02:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Leaving the single 10 yen coin above, we drop the three below.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.44,0:02:55.19,white-small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(185,82)}don't drop
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.00,0:02:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,In this way we can confirm whether the three coins have changed position.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.00,0:02:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Will the 1 yen coin end up at the bottom?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.00,0:03:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The 1 yen coin ended up in the middle.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.00,0:03:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's try once more.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.00,0:03:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The result is the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.00,0:03:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's try to organize this on paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.00,0:03:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,When we started 1 yen  then 10 yen became 10 yen then 1 yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.00,0:03:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Next if we added another 10 yen coin below.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.00,0:03:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It changed  like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.00,0:03:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not very clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.00,0:03:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What will happen with a different arrangement of coins?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.00,0:03:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This time we drop with the 1 yen coin in the middle.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.98,0:03:56.38,white-small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(183,80)}doesn't drop
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.00,0:04:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And it ended up underneath.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.00,0:04:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's also record this on paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.00,0:04:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Looking carefully at the results...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.00,0:04:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,A pattern is visible.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.00,0:04:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Given this, what will happen with this arrangement?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.00,0:04:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Thinking Observation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.24,0:05:00.05,white-large,,0,0,0,,{\pos(561.778,222)}Thinking\NObservation
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.68,0:05:07.82,black-large,,0,0,0,,{\pos(243.556,46.889)}Dedenion
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.68,0:05:07.82,white-large,,0,0,0,,{\pos(429.334,67.334)}On Summer Vacation
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.68,0:05:07.82,black-large,,0,0,0,,{\pos(437.334,341.112)}This time, we're resting.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.82,0:05:12.06,white-large,,0,0,0,,{\pos(329.778,103.778)}Today's Discovery
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.82,0:05:12.06,white-large,,0,0,0,,{\pos(386.667,257.556)}Holes in the Ground
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.06,0:05:15.69,white-large,,0,0,0,,Not worth mentioning
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.69,0:05:18.60,white-large,,0,0,0,,but still I want to tell it to someone
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.60,0:05:22.37,white-large,,0,0,0,,today's discovery
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.37,0:05:25.77,white-large,,0,0,0,,casually looking beneath a roadside tree
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.77,0:05:28.74,white-large,,0,0,0,,there's a many holes of some kind
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.74,0:05:30.88,white-large,,0,0,0,,what are these holes?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.38,0:05:45.82,white-large,,0,0,0,,{\pos(334.222,105.555)}Q: Shihara-kun  later found something and understood why the holes were there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.58,0:05:45.82,white-large,,0,0,0,,{\pos(281.778,279.777)}What do you think he found?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.82,0:05:53.23,white-large,,0,0,0,,How wonderful. Today's discovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.23,0:05:58.50,white-large,,0,0,0,,And tomorrow there will probably be another.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.20,0:06:05.28,black-large,,0,0,0,,{\pos(358.222,41.556)}one each day
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.20,0:06:05.28,black-large,,0,0,0,,{\pos(422.222,158.889)}today's discovery
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.00,0:06:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We will reveal the answer in the next program.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.64,0:06:13.28,white-large,,0,0,0,,{\pos(278.222,254)}Yu Aoi's\NThinking Practice
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.00,0:06:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Today's problem uses a pendulum.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.00,0:06:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If we pull back the pendulum
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.00,0:06:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, it swings well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.00,0:06:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a pendulum.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.00,0:06:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, the pendulum we're using is special.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.00,0:06:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The weight at the end is a powerful magnet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.00,0:06:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If we bring it close to some paper clips.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.00,0:06:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They stick to it firmly.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.00,0:06:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we have prepared an aluminum plate.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.00,0:07:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And this plate
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.00,0:07:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't stick to the magnet at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.00,0:07:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Magnets don't stick to aluminum.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.00,0:07:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now this is the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.00,0:07:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The aluminum plate that this magnet will not stick to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.00,0:07:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we place it on the desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.00,0:07:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And we separate the magnet from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.00,0:07:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If we do this how will the pendulum swing?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.00,0:07:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,1. It will go slower than the case with no plate.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.13,0:07:50.52,white-small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(182.223,99.333)}1. It will slow down and soon stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.74,0:07:50.52,white-small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(191.112,152.666)}2. It will speed up and not stop at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.08,0:07:50.52,white-small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(168.001,209.555)}3. The swing will not change.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.00,0:07:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and quickly come to a stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.00,0:07:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,2. Just the opposite. It will go faster and not stop at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.00,0:07:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,3. It will swing the same as if there were no plate.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.00,0:07:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then what will happen?\NWe'll present the anser at the end of the program.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.00,0:07:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, please think hard won't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.71,0:08:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Observation, hypothesis, experiment and then reflection.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.51,0:08:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Thinking scientifically. Thinking Crow.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.94,0:08:18.98,white-large,,0,0,0,,{\pos(322.667,44.222)}Thinking Crow
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.94,0:08:18.98,white-small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(320,135.778)}thinking scientifically
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.94,0:08:18.98,white-small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(114.667,307.333)}Spiny Lobster larva
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.98,0:08:29.99,black-small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(241.777,114.445)}Q. What will happen to the magnetic pendulum?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.64,0:08:29.99,black-small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(370.666,193.556)}1. It will slow down and soon stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.64,0:08:29.99,black-small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(378.666,248.667)}2. It will speed up and not stop at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.64,0:08:29.99,black-small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(343.999,305.556)}3. Its swing won't change.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.00,0:08:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And now the answer from earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.00,0:08:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone did you think carefully?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.00,0:08:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, let's do it for real.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.00,0:08:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,First we try the case without the plate beneath.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.00,0:08:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the normal state.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.00,0:08:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we try with the aluminum plate beneath.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.00,0:09:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you think the pendulum will swing?\NWatch really closely, won't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.00,0:09:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It stopped right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.00,0:09:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's try once more.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.00,0:09:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The answer is 1.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.00,0:09:27.65,white-small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(312,282.444)}1. It  will slow down and soon stop...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.00,0:09:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The pendulum swings more slowly than without the plate.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.00,0:09:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and stops right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.00,0:09:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But magnets ought not stick to aluminum.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.00,0:09:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Why should this happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.00,0:09:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This is related to a property between magnets and aluminum.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.00,0:09:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Magnets don't stick to aluminum, but aluminum conducts electricity.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.00,0:09:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And magnets are electric...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.00,0:09:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,From here on we think for ourselves.
